---
import SlideLayout from "../layouts/SlideLayout.astro";
import Slide from "../components/Slide.astro";

const TOTAL = 14;
---

<SlideLayout title="Listening · Anthropic Cultural Exchange Hackathon">
  {/* ─────────────────────────────── 01 · TITLE ─────────────────────────────── */}
  <Slide bg="paper" page={1} total={TOTAL}>
    <div style="flex:1; display:flex; flex-direction:column; justify-content:center;">
      <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 1.2rem;">
        Anthropic Cultural Exchange Hackathon · 2026
      </div>
      <h1 class="serif" style="font-size: clamp(3.8rem, 8.4vw, 7.6rem); line-height: 0.95; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin: 0;">
        <span class="zh" style="font-size: 0.72em; color: var(--sun); margin-right: 0.16em; vertical-align: -0.04em;">听</span>Listening.
      </h1>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-top: 0.6rem; font-size: clamp(0.9rem, 1.1vw, 1.05rem); letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase;">
        <span class="zh" style="color: var(--ink);">听</span> · <em style="font-style: normal; color: var(--ink-500);">tīng</em> · the act of listening
      </p>
      <hr class="divider" style="margin-top: 1.6rem; margin-bottom: 1.6rem; width: 80px;" />
      <p class="lede" style="max-width: 56ch; font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 1.6vw, 1.55rem);">
        A mobile audiobook that turns your commute into a Chinese-learning loop —
        classical works narrated, idioms unpacked, and your spoken answers graded
        by Claude.
      </p>
      <div style="margin-top: 2rem; display:flex; gap: 0.6rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <span class="chip"><span class="dot"></span> Claude Haiku 4.5 + Sonnet 4.5</span>
        <span class="chip"><span class="dot" style="background: var(--gold)"></span> ElevenLabs TTS</span>
        <span class="chip"><span class="dot" style="background: var(--jade)"></span> Next.js 15 · PWA</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Slide>

  {/* ─────────────────────────────── 02 · THE PROMPT ─────────────────────────────── */}
  <Slide bg="rose" page={2} total={TOTAL}>
    <div class="eyebrow">Prompt</div>
    <div style="flex:1; display:flex; flex-direction:column; justify-content:center; max-width: 64ch;">
      <p class="serif" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2.1rem); line-height: 1.3; color: var(--ink); margin: 0 0 1.4rem 0;">
        As AI handles routine work, questions about human purpose become urgent.
        Access to creative development and cultural preservation isn't equal.
        People who could find meaning through creative expression often don't get
        the chance.
      </p>
      <p class="serif" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2.1rem); line-height: 1.3; color: var(--ink); margin: 0;">
        Build something that
        <span style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--ink);">amplifies human creativity, helps people find meaning, or supports cultural expression and preservation</span>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Slide>

  {/* ─────────────────────────────── 03 · THE GAP ─────────────────────────────── */}
  <Slide bg="paper" page={3} total={TOTAL}>
    <div class="eyebrow">The gap we keep hitting</div>
    <h2 class="title" style="margin-top: 0.6rem; max-width: 18ch;">
      Classical Chinese literature is locked behind <span style="color: var(--sun);">three doors.</span>
    </h2>
    <hr class="divider" />
    <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top: 2.2rem;">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="tag tag-sun">01</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="font-size: 1.55rem; margin: 0.7rem 0 0.4rem;">Language</h3>
        <p class="body muted">
          The original text uses literary <span class="zh">文言文</span> with rare characters and
          context-dependent grammar. Hard, even for native speakers.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="tag tag-gold">02</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="font-size: 1.55rem; margin: 0.7rem 0 0.4rem;">Culture</h3>
        <p class="body muted">
          Idioms like <span class="zh">知己知彼</span> are surface phrases; their meaning lives in 2500
          years of military and political reference.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="tag tag-jade">03</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="font-size: 1.55rem; margin: 0.7rem 0 0.4rem;">Practice</h3>
        <p class="body muted">
          Reading is passive. Real fluency requires speaking, recall, and a
          patient interlocutor who never gets tired of you stumbling.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="body muted" style="margin-top: 2rem; max-width: 70ch;">
      Listening treats all three as a single audio surface: a narrator reads, idioms
      annotate themselves as they're spoken, and Claude pauses the story to ask
      and grade — all from one screen, on a phone, hands-free.
    </p>
  </Slide>

  {/* ─────────────────────────────── 04 · THE SOLUTION ─────────────────────────────── */}
  <Slide bg="blue" page={4} total={TOTAL}>
    <div class="eyebrow">The solution</div>
    <h2 class="title" style="margin-top: 0.6rem;">
      An audiobook that <span style="color: var(--sun);">talks back.</span>
    </h2>
    <hr class="divider" />
    <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top: 1.8rem; gap: 1.6rem;">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow">01 · Voice check-ins</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.4rem;">Pause, ask, listen.</h3>
        <p class="body muted" style="font-size: 0.95rem;">
          Every few minutes the narration fades. Claude asks a comprehension
          question. You speak the answer — in English or Chinese — and the model
          grades you before the book resumes.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow">02 · Cultural pop-ups</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.4rem;">Idioms in their world.</h3>
        <p class="body muted" style="font-size: 0.95rem;">
          Chéngyǔ and historical references trigger a card the moment they're
          spoken — literal meaning, cultural meaning, and the story behind it.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow">03 · Personal vault</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.4rem;">Save what sticks.</h3>
        <p class="body muted" style="font-size: 0.95rem;">
          Tap once to save a sentence. It becomes a smart flashcard with the
          audio snippet, pinyin, and meaning — stored on-device.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="body muted" style="margin-top: 2rem; max-width: 70ch;">
      Today's library: <span class="zh" style="color: var(--ink);">孙子兵法</span> — Sun Tzu's
      <em>Art of War</em>, 13 chapters, fully narrated, fully annotated.
    </p>
  </Slide>

  {/* ───────────────── 05 · TECHNICAL OVERVIEW (HIGHLIGHTED) ───────────────── */}
  <Slide bg="ink" page={5} total={TOTAL}>
    <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap: 12px;">
      <span class="tag tag-sun">TECHNICAL EXECUTION</span>
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: rgba(243,238,224,0.5);">Architecture overview</span>
    </div>
    <h2 class="title" style="margin-top: 0.6rem; color: var(--ink-50);">
      One audio file. <span style="color: var(--sun);">Five Claude touchpoints.</span> Zero servers.
    </h2>
    <hr class="divider" style="margin-top: 1.4rem;" />
    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin-top: 1.4rem; flex: 1;">
      <div class="code" style="margin: 0;">
<span class="tok-mute"># Runtime data flow ──────────────────────────────────</span>

[Audiobook MP3 + transcript]
        │
        ├── timestamp event ──► <span class="tok-fn">/api/translate</span>     <span class="tok-mute">(Haiku 4.5)</span>
        │                          → idiom pop-up card
        │
        ├── smart pause   ───► <span class="tok-fn">/api/question</span>      <span class="tok-mute">(Haiku 4.5)</span>
        │                          → text-to-speech via
        │                            <span class="tok-fn">/api/speak</span>   <span class="tok-mute">(ElevenLabs)</span>
        │
        ├── user speaks   ───► <span class="tok-fn">/api/transcribe</span>    <span class="tok-mute">(Whisper)</span>
        │                          → <span class="tok-fn">/api/grade</span>   <span class="tok-mute">(Sonnet 4.5)</span>
        │                            → verdict + feedback
        │
        └── tap "save"    ───► IndexedDB vault   <span class="tok-mute">(idb-keyval)</span>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap: 0.9rem;">
        <div class="card-dark">
          <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--code-jade);">FRONTEND</div>
          <div class="body" style="color: var(--ink-50); font-size: 0.95rem; margin-top: 4px;">
            Next.js 15 · React 19 RC · Tailwind · PWA<br />
            Web Speech API (mic capture, on-device)
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-dark">
          <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--code-gold);">MODELS</div>
          <div class="body" style="color: var(--ink-50); font-size: 0.95rem; margin-top: 4px;">
            Claude <strong>Haiku 4.5</strong> — translation, questions<br />
            Claude <strong>Sonnet 4.5</strong> — grading spoken answers
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-dark">
          <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--code-accent);">AUDIO</div>
          <div class="body" style="color: var(--ink-50); font-size: 0.95rem; margin-top: 4px;">
            ElevenLabs Multilingual v2 (TTS, zh-CN)<br />
            Whisper transcription on user replies
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Slide>

  {/* ───────────────── 06 · MODEL ORCHESTRATION (HIGHLIGHTED) ───────────────── */}
  <Slide bg="ink" page={6} total={TOTAL}>
    <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap: 12px;">
      <span class="tag tag-sun">TECHNICAL EXECUTION</span>
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: rgba(243,238,224,0.5);">Claude model orchestration</span>
    </div>
    <h2 class="title" style="margin-top: 0.6rem; color: var(--ink-50);">
      Two models. <span style="color: var(--sun);">One reading session.</span>
    </h2>
    <hr class="divider" style="margin-top: 1.4rem;" />
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top: 1.4rem; flex: 1;">
      <div class="card-dark">
        <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center;">
          <span class="tag" style="background: var(--gold);">HAIKU 4.5 · FAST</span>
          <span class="mono" style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--code-mute);">~200ms p50</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="font-size: 1.45rem; color: var(--ink-50); margin: 0.8rem 0 0.5rem;">High-volume, low-stakes</h3>
        <ul class="body" style="color: var(--ink-100); font-size: 0.95rem; padding-left: 1.1rem; margin: 0;">
          <li>Idiom translation (<code class="mono">/api/translate</code>)</li>
          <li>Comprehension question generation (<code class="mono">/api/question</code>)</li>
          <li>Per-chapter transcript enrichment (offline batch)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="body" style="color: var(--code-mute); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 0.9rem;">
          Called dozens of times per session. Cheap, fast, idempotent.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-dark">
        <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center;">
          <span class="tag" style="background: var(--sun);">SONNET 4.5 · SMART</span>
          <span class="mono" style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--code-mute);">~1.4s p50</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="font-size: 1.45rem; color: var(--ink-50); margin: 0.8rem 0 0.5rem;">Rare, high-judgment</h3>
        <ul class="body" style="color: var(--ink-100); font-size: 0.95rem; padding-left: 1.1rem; margin: 0;">
          <li>Grading spoken answers (<code class="mono">/api/grade</code>)</li>
          <li>4-tier verdict: great · good · partial · off</li>
          <li>Tone-aware feedback: encouraging, second-person, ≤30 words</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="body" style="color: var(--code-mute); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 0.9rem;">
          Called once per check-in. Worth the latency for nuanced judgment.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="body" style="color: var(--code-mute); margin-top: 1.4rem; max-width: 80ch;">
      <strong style="color: var(--ink-50);">Why split?</strong> A single Sonnet call costs ~7× more and runs ~7× slower than Haiku. By
      routing 80%+ of requests to Haiku and reserving Sonnet for the one moment that needs
      pedagogical judgment, the app stays under $0.01 per learning session.
    </p>
  </Slide>

  {/* ───────────────── 07 · VOICE PIPELINE (HIGHLIGHTED) ───────────────── */}
  <Slide bg="ink" page={7} total={TOTAL}>
    <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap: 12px;">
      <span class="tag tag-sun">TECHNICAL EXECUTION</span>
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: rgba(243,238,224,0.5);">Voice loop: TTS ↔ STT ↔ Claude</span>
    </div>
    <h2 class="title" style="margin-top: 0.6rem; color: var(--ink-50);">
      A round-trip in <span style="color: var(--sun);">≈2.4 seconds.</span>
    </h2>
    <hr class="divider" style="margin-top: 1.4rem;" />
    <div class="code" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
<span class="tok-mute">// /api/question · Claude Haiku 4.5</span>
const resp = await client.messages.create(&#123;
  model: MODELS.fast,
  system: <span class="tok-str">"You are a warm Chinese listening tutor. Generate ONE
           short comprehension question (≤18 words)…"</span>,
  messages: [&#123; role: <span class="tok-str">"user"</span>, content: recentContext &#125;],
&#125;);

<span class="tok-mute">// /api/speak · ElevenLabs Multilingual v2</span>
await elevenlabs.textToSpeech.<span class="tok-fn">convert</span>(voiceId, &#123;
  text: question, model_id: <span class="tok-str">"eleven_multilingual_v2"</span>,
&#125;);

<span class="tok-mute">// Browser · Web Speech API (no upload — runs on-device)</span>
const recognition = new <span class="tok-fn">webkitSpeechRecognition</span>();
recognition.lang = answerLanguage === <span class="tok-str">"zh"</span> ? <span class="tok-str">"zh-CN"</span> : <span class="tok-str">"en-US"</span>;

<span class="tok-mute">// /api/grade · Claude Sonnet 4.5</span>
const verdict = await client.messages.create(&#123;
  model: MODELS.smart,
  system: <span class="tok-str">"Return JSON: &#123;verdict: great|good|partial|off, feedback,
           modelAnswer&#125;. Be kind on 'off' — redirect, don't shame."</span>,
  messages: [&#123; role: <span class="tok-str">"user"</span>, content: <span class="tok-fn">buildGradingPrompt</span>(...) &#125;],
&#125;);
    </div>
    <p class="body" style="color: var(--code-mute); margin-top: 1.2rem;">
      The mic stays on-device via Web Speech API — no raw audio leaves the phone. Only the
      transcribed answer (a short string) is sent for grading.
    </p>
  </Slide>

  {/* ───────────────── 08 · DATA PIPELINE (HIGHLIGHTED) ───────────────── */}
  <Slide bg="ink" page={8} total={TOTAL}>
    <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap: 12px;">
      <span class="tag tag-sun">TECHNICAL EXECUTION</span>
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: rgba(243,238,224,0.5);">Offline enrichment pipeline</span>
    </div>
    <h2 class="title" style="margin-top: 0.6rem; color: var(--ink-50);">
      The book is <span style="color: var(--sun);">pre-chewed</span> before you press play.
    </h2>
    <hr class="divider" style="margin-top: 1.4rem;" />
    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1.2rem; margin-top: 1.4rem; flex: 1;">
      <div class="card-dark">
        <div class="mono" style="color: var(--code-jade); font-size: 0.78rem;">scripts/prepare-chapters.ts</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="color: var(--ink-50); font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 0.7rem 0 0.4rem;">1 · Segment</h3>
        <p class="body" style="color: var(--ink-100); font-size: 0.88rem; line-height: 1.45;">
          Raw <span class="zh">孙子兵法</span> text → 13 chapter JSONs, sentence-tokenized
          with stable IDs.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-dark">
        <div class="mono" style="color: var(--code-jade); font-size: 0.78rem;">scripts/enrich-translations.ts</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="color: var(--ink-50); font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 0.7rem 0 0.4rem;">2 · Enrich</h3>
        <p class="body" style="color: var(--ink-100); font-size: 0.88rem; line-height: 1.45;">
          Each sentence → Claude → pinyin + word gloss + English + idiom flags.
          Cached. Resumable.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-dark">
        <div class="mono" style="color: var(--code-jade); font-size: 0.78rem;">scripts/generate-audio.ts</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="color: var(--ink-50); font-size: 1.25rem; margin: 0.7rem 0 0.4rem;">3 · Narrate</h3>
        <p class="body" style="color: var(--ink-100); font-size: 0.88rem; line-height: 1.45;">
          Sentence text → ElevenLabs → per-chapter MP3 with sentence-level
          timestamps for the player.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="body" style="color: var(--code-mute); margin-top: 1.4rem; max-width: 88ch;">
      <strong style="color: var(--ink-50);">Why offline?</strong> Translating
      a 6,000-character book at runtime would burn $$ and seconds for every user.
      One Claude pass per sentence at build time → infinite playback at near-zero
      cost. The output is plain JSON shipped in <code class="mono">public/chapters/*.json</code>.
    </p>
  </Slide>

  {/* ───────────────── 09 · OFFLINE-FIRST / PWA (HIGHLIGHTED) ───────────────── */}
  <Slide bg="ink" page={9} total={TOTAL}>
    <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap: 12px;">
      <span class="tag tag-sun">TECHNICAL EXECUTION</span>
      <span class="eyebrow" style="color: rgba(243,238,224,0.5);">PWA, on-device state, privacy</span>
    </div>
    <h2 class="title" style="margin-top: 0.6rem; color: var(--ink-50);">
      Your phone is the <span style="color: var(--sun);">server.</span>
    </h2>
    <hr class="divider" style="margin-top: 1.4rem;" />
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top: 1.4rem; flex: 1; gap: 1.6rem;">
      <div class="card-dark">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--code-jade);">Storage</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="color: var(--ink-50); font-size: 1.35rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.4rem;">
          IndexedDB via <code class="mono" style="font-size:0.82em;">idb-keyval</code>
        </h3>
        <ul class="body" style="color: var(--ink-100); font-size: 0.9rem; padding-left: 1.1rem; margin: 0.4rem 0 0;">
          <li>Vault entries (saved sentences + audio + pinyin)</li>
          <li>Playback position per chapter</li>
          <li>User settings (language preference, check-in cadence)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card-dark">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--code-gold);">Network</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="color: var(--ink-50); font-size: 1.35rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.4rem;">
          API calls only on demand
        </h3>
        <ul class="body" style="color: var(--ink-100); font-size: 0.9rem; padding-left: 1.1rem; margin: 0.4rem 0 0;">
          <li>Chapter assets cached once → offline playback</li>
          <li>Claude calls only when user triggers a check-in</li>
          <li>Subway-safe: failures degrade gracefully to "read mode"</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card-dark">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--code-accent);">Privacy</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="color: var(--ink-50); font-size: 1.35rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.4rem;">
          Mic capture stays local
        </h3>
        <ul class="body" style="color: var(--ink-100); font-size: 0.9rem; padding-left: 1.1rem; margin: 0.4rem 0 0;">
          <li>Web Speech API transcribes in-browser</li>
          <li>Only the text (rarely &gt;30 words) is sent to Claude</li>
          <li>No accounts, no telemetry, no audio uploads</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card-dark">
        <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--ink-100);">Install</div>
        <h3 class="serif" style="color: var(--ink-50); font-size: 1.35rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.4rem;">
          Add to Home Screen
        </h3>
        <ul class="body" style="color: var(--ink-100); font-size: 0.9rem; padding-left: 1.1rem; margin: 0.4rem 0 0;">
          <li>One install — no app store</li>
          <li>Runs in iOS / Android Safari, Chrome, Firefox</li>
          <li>Background audio + lockscreen controls (Media Session API)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Slide>

  {/* ─────────────────────────────── 10 · IMPACT ─────────────────────────────── */}
  <Slide bg="sand" page={10} total={TOTAL}>
    <div class="eyebrow">Impact potential</div>
    <h2 class="title" style="margin-top: 0.6rem; max-width: 20ch;">
      A loop that fits in the gaps of a day.
    </h2>
    <hr class="divider" />
    <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <div>
        <div class="serif" style="font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 4vw, 3.4rem); color: var(--sun); line-height: 1;">30M+</div>
        <div class="body muted" style="margin-top: 0.6rem;">
          adult learners studying Mandarin worldwide — the largest second-language
          cohort, and the one most starved of audio practice with native cultural framing.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="serif" style="font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 4vw, 3.4rem); color: var(--gold); line-height: 1;">2500</div>
        <div class="body muted" style="margin-top: 0.6rem;">
          years of <span class="zh">孙子兵法</span> commentary, idioms, and historical
          reference — currently locked away from anyone without a graduate-level reading
          ability or a private tutor.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="serif" style="font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 4vw, 3.4rem); color: var(--jade); line-height: 1;">~$0.01</div>
        <div class="body muted" style="margin-top: 0.6rem;">
          marginal cost per learning session today, thanks to the Haiku/Sonnet split and
          offline enrichment. Every commute becomes a tutor session.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="body" style="margin-top: 2rem; max-width: 78ch; color: var(--ink-700);">
      The shape generalizes. Swap the book and you have <em>Beowulf</em>, the
      <em>Mahābhārata</em>, <em>Don Quixote</em> — any text whose audio + cultural layer
      has never been affordable to package together.
    </p>
  </Slide>

  {/* ─────────────────────────────── 11 · ETHICAL ALIGNMENT ─────────────────────────────── */}
  <Slide bg="rose" page={11} total={TOTAL}>
    <div class="eyebrow">Ethical alignment</div>
    <h2 class="title" style="margin-top: 0.6rem;">
      The model is the <span style="color: var(--sun);">tutor</span>, never the <em>learner</em>.
    </h2>
    <hr class="divider" />
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top: 1.6rem; gap: 1.6rem;">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow">Empowering, not replacing</div>
        <p class="body" style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">
          Claude generates <em>questions</em> for you to answer — it doesn't generate
          paraphrases that pretend to be your understanding. The act of speaking the
          answer is yours, and ungeneratable by the model.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow">Respect the source culture</div>
        <p class="body" style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">
          The Chinese text is presented in its original form, with translation as a
          scaffold — not a replacement. Idiom cards show <em>literal → cultural →
          historical</em>, so the learner ends up closer to the source, not further from it.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow">Kind by default</div>
        <p class="body" style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">
          The grading prompt requires <strong>encouraging, second-person feedback
          ≤30 words</strong>. The "off" verdict is required to <em>gently redirect, don't
          shame</em>. Learning is fragile; the system reflects that.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow">Privacy as a feature</div>
        <p class="body" style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">
          No accounts. No telemetry. Audio is captured on-device via Web Speech API; only
          transcribed text leaves the phone. The vault lives in IndexedDB — you can wipe
          it with a single button.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Slide>

